Package: multiGGM
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Inference of Multiple Gaussian Graphical Models
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Christine B.", family = "Peterson", role = c("aut")),
    person(given = "First", family = "Last", role = c("cre"), email = "first.last@example.com"))
Description: Utilities and MCMC implementation for Bayesian inference of multiple
    Gaussian graphical models. Supports G-Wishart (Peterson, Stingo, and
    Vannucci, 2015, JASA), scalable spike-and-slab (Shaddox et al., 2018,
    Stat Biosci), and multi-platform spike-and-slab (Shaddox et al., 2020,
    Biostatistics) methods. The multi-platform extension jointly models networks
    across multiple data types with a hierarchical MRF coupling group similarity
    across platforms. Includes MRF-coupled edge priors for borrowing strength
    across groups, parallel multi-chain orchestration, and helpers to convert
    precision matrices to partial correlations.
